name: Indonesian President
summary: Prabowo Subianto has been sworn in as Indonesia's eighth president, with a focus on foreign policy and a vow to combat corruption. Despite democratic fatigue, Prabowo has appointed the largest cabinet since the 1960s. His presidency has already garnered attention from international media, with Al Jazeera emphasizing his anti-corruption stance, VOA Asia highlighting his foreign policy focus, and The Conversation Indonesia expressing concern about the potential impact of his views on democracy. Reuters and The Associated Press provide further details on Prabowo's background as a former general and his commitment to tackling corruption. The BBC reports on the size of his cabinet, while Foreign Affairs Magazine delves into his complex political history. Yahoo Canada Finance and Bowen Island Undercurrent cover the swearing-in ceremony, and China Daily acknowledges Subianto as Indonesia's eighth president.
